WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
<i>[This program is suitable
for viewers ages 15 and up.]</i>

2
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

3
00:00:56.023 --> 00:00:57.228
Jae Beom.

4
00:00:57.733 --> 00:00:59.965
Take the next flight
coming back to Korea.

5
00:01:00.484 --> 00:01:01.793
Soo Jin...

6
00:01:02.456 --> 00:01:04.142
just walked in.

7
00:01:13.352 --> 00:01:15.034
You're here?

8
00:01:15.034 --> 00:01:17.001
Have you been doing well?

9
00:01:19.373 --> 00:01:22.183
I'm so shocked that
I'm at a loss for words.

10
00:01:25.618 --> 00:01:27.719
So you speak, instead.

11
00:01:31.404 --> 00:01:33.028
Have you been doing well?

12
00:01:33.989 --> 00:01:36.144
How have you been doing up until now?

13
00:01:36.861 --> 00:01:41.573
You're still wearing the coat that
I bought you 10 years ago, I see.

14
00:01:57.289 --> 00:01:59.104
I have a favor to ask of you.

15
00:02:00.241 --> 00:02:02.211
So that's why you came.

16
00:02:03.386 --> 00:02:05.162
I need money.

17
00:02:06.855 --> 00:02:08.425
How much?

18
00:02:08.425 --> 00:02:10.134
10 million won.

19
00:02:12.164 --> 00:02:13.783
Are you ill?

20
00:02:13.783 --> 00:02:15.135
No.

21
00:02:18.916 --> 00:02:20.773
Did you cause trouble, then?

22
00:02:22.138 --> 00:02:26.937
You never asked me for even
10,000 won after becoming an adult

23
00:02:26.937 --> 00:02:30.693
and you insisted on paying for
your own meals, no matter what

24
00:02:30.693 --> 00:02:32.194
so, what's going on?

25
00:02:33.015 --> 00:02:37.183
What on earth had to happen that
you'd come to me to borrow money?

26
00:02:37.707 --> 00:02:39.501
Can't you just...

27
00:02:42.648 --> 00:02:45.575
not ask me anything and
lend it to me, just this once?

28
00:02:49.426 --> 00:02:51.229
Do you want it in cash?

29
00:02:51.229 --> 00:02:52.926
Or as a bank transfer?

30
00:02:53.785 --> 00:02:55.766
Cash, please.

31
00:03:29.423 --> 00:03:31.204
I have one condition.

32
00:03:35.147 --> 00:03:37.296
Meet with me just 10 times.

33
00:03:38.121 --> 00:03:40.140
Every time you meet with me...

34
00:03:40.718 --> 00:03:42.752
I'll give you a million won.

35
00:03:42.752 --> 00:03:44.096
How does that sound?

36
00:04:02.812 --> 00:04:04.607
My mom...

37
00:04:05.108 --> 00:04:06.702
will come.

38
00:04:06.702 --> 00:04:08.846
She's not the kind of person
who wouldn't come.

39
00:04:10.370 --> 00:04:12.302
Where do you live?

40
00:04:14.521 --> 00:04:16.011
Um...

41
00:04:16.514 --> 00:04:17.850
a sauna?

42
00:04:18.389 --> 00:04:19.963
Do you know about saunas?

43
00:04:19.963 --> 00:04:21.598
They're so nice!

44
00:04:21.598 --> 00:04:23.281
You don't have a home?

45
00:04:23.281 --> 00:04:24.944
I was told we'd find one soon.

46
00:04:31.716 --> 00:04:34.944
But... what is this sound?

47
00:04:35.735 --> 00:04:38.954
Jingle... jangle.

48
00:04:40.555 --> 00:04:42.038
Hello.

49
00:04:42.038 --> 00:04:43.382
Ah, yes. Please take
a seat over there.

50
00:04:43.382 --> 00:04:44.420
Sure.

51
00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:46.439
Get me a chemotherapy appointment.

52
00:04:47.156 --> 00:04:49.351
I feel like I'll be able to do it
all of the sudden.

53
00:04:51.398 --> 00:04:54.324
When will I find out whether or
not I'll be able to get surgery?

54
00:05:02.776 --> 00:05:04.771
I waited for you.

55
00:05:04.771 --> 00:05:06.146
I know.

56
00:05:41.163 --> 00:05:42.766
Yoon Bok!

57
00:05:45.625 --> 00:05:47.288
Yoon Bok?

58
00:05:48.225 --> 00:05:49.701
Yoon Bok.

59
00:05:53.223 --> 00:05:55.177
Did I surprise you?

60
00:05:58.831 --> 00:06:00.531
Mom!

61
00:06:00.531 --> 00:06:02.298
What is it, Hye Na?

62
00:06:06.360 --> 00:06:09.322
Have you ever seen such nice towels?

63
00:06:18.939 --> 00:06:21.050
Where has she been all this time?

64
00:06:21.050 --> 00:06:22.314
Let's...

65
00:06:22.944 --> 00:06:25.064
all eat dinner together tomorrow.

66
00:06:27.324 --> 00:06:29.843
Don't ask her where she's been.

67
00:06:29.843 --> 00:06:35.471
Or why she came, why she left,
or what she plans to do now, either.

68
00:06:35.471 --> 00:06:40.636
And definitely don't tell her
that I have cancer.

69
00:06:40.636 --> 00:06:43.680
What am I supposed to talk to
her about, then? The weather?

70
00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:44.776
Politics?

71
00:06:44.776 --> 00:06:47.071
Or celebrity gossip,
as if we're just acquaintances?

72
00:06:47.071 --> 00:06:48.853
About the fact that you got married.

73
00:06:49.579 --> 00:06:52.216
About how you almost died
giving birth to twins.

74
00:06:52.826 --> 00:06:54.970
About how your mother-in-law is peculiar.

75
00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:56.355
And...

76
00:06:57.110 --> 00:06:59.432
the cat you guys are raising is cute.

77
00:06:59.901 --> 00:07:03.254
And about how you almost
got divorced last year.

78
00:07:05.442 --> 00:07:06.480
Hey!

79
00:07:06.480 --> 00:07:08.101
Be quiet, you guys!

80
00:07:10.077 --> 00:07:12.963
You weren't scared of the lady
at the barber shop?

81
00:07:14.564 --> 00:07:16.694
Why would I be scared?

82
00:07:18.490 --> 00:07:21.430
Kids used to be really scared
of her when I was young.

83
00:07:22.374 --> 00:07:24.271
That lady...

84
00:07:25.278 --> 00:07:27.516
is missing a pinky.

85
00:07:28.108 --> 00:07:29.288
Did you see it?

86
00:07:30.151 --> 00:07:31.672
Really?

87
00:07:32.173 --> 00:07:35.024
There are rumors that
she lost it while in prison.

88
00:07:35.846 --> 00:07:38.189
And some say that she killed someone.

89
00:07:39.851 --> 00:07:41.697
When I was young

90
00:07:41.697 --> 00:07:43.966
guys would go into the barber shop

91
00:07:43.966 --> 00:07:46.473
and yell, "Murderer!"

92
00:07:46.473 --> 00:07:49.365
as a test of courage.

93
00:07:51.766 --> 00:07:55.718
I had to pass by it every day
on my way home.

94
00:07:56.636 --> 00:07:59.701
When I saw the sign for the
barber shop from far away...

95
00:08:00.216 --> 00:08:03.509
I got so scared that I started running.

96
00:08:03.509 --> 00:08:06.161
I feel so sorry for that lady.

97
00:08:37.342 --> 00:08:38.918
<i>Miss Ye Eun.</i>

98
00:08:38.918 --> 00:08:42.105
<i>I am hoping that I won't be
needing to send you this letter.</i>

99
00:08:42.706 --> 00:08:47.668
<i>Because I am only planning
to send you this letter</i>

100
00:08:47.668 --> 00:08:50.929
<i>if Hye Na and I couldn't escape
this country safely, as planned.</i>

101
00:08:52.788 --> 00:08:54.831
<i>What I fear the most right now</i>

102
00:08:54.831 --> 00:08:58.244
<i>isn't that I'll be arrested
for kidnapping</i>

103
00:08:58.244 --> 00:09:02.493
<i>but that things go wrong, and Hye Na will
have to return to her mom and that man.</i>

104
00:09:03.038 --> 00:09:05.855
<i>Please look over the materials
that I've sent you</i>

105
00:09:05.855 --> 00:09:10.462
<i>and please help us so that Hye Na
will not have to return to those people.</i>

106
00:09:10.462 --> 00:09:14.888
<i>I don't think there is a person
who could do this better than you.</i>

107
00:09:16.038 --> 00:09:20.419
<i>I won't resent you even if
you report me to the cops.</i>

108
00:09:21.149 --> 00:09:24.210
<i>Please take care of this
matter as you see fit.</i>

109
00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:25.434
<i>[Kim Hye Na]</i>

110
00:09:25.946 --> 00:09:27.469
This way.

111
00:09:27.980 --> 00:09:31.652
A lot of people worry about their safety
with these types of homes.

112
00:09:31.652 --> 00:09:33.787
But you needn't worry
about that here.

113
00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:37.730
Because as you can see,
the police station is right up front.

114
00:09:42.254 --> 00:09:43.389
Um...

115
00:09:43.888 --> 00:09:45.907
do you have any other
homes available?

116
00:09:46.652 --> 00:09:48.168
Please come in.

117
00:09:50.894 --> 00:09:52.644
Take a look around.

118
00:09:55.768 --> 00:09:57.828
How long are you looking
to stay here?

119
00:09:57.828 --> 00:09:59.909
At the very least,
half a month.

120
00:09:59.909 --> 00:10:01.673
And no longer than two months.

121
00:10:01.673 --> 00:10:04.807
Goodness, not even three months,
but just one or two months?

122
00:10:04.807 --> 00:10:06.629
I'll give you two months'
worth of rent up front.

123
00:10:06.629 --> 00:10:09.152
The owner won't want to do that.

124
00:10:09.152 --> 00:10:11.181
Because if you live here for only
two months, but ruin the floor

125
00:10:11.181 --> 00:10:13.441
it'll be a huge nuisance for them.

126
00:10:13.441 --> 00:10:15.131
And you have a kid, to boot!

127
00:10:16.650 --> 00:10:19.701
You should look into a student hostel
or something, instead.

128
00:10:19.701 --> 00:10:22.306
Other real estate brokers
will tell you the same thing.

129
00:10:37.485 --> 00:10:39.952
"To Oh Cheol, in Heaven."

130
00:10:39.952 --> 00:10:42.357
"Oh Cheol,
I'm Kim Hye Na from Class 1-3."

131
00:10:42.357 --> 00:10:44.208
"Where are you right now?"

132
00:10:44.208 --> 00:10:46.080
"Do you not feel any pain anymore?"

133
00:10:46.080 --> 00:10:49.072
"I want to go there, too."

134
00:10:49.072 --> 00:10:50.320
<i>Dear Miss Soo Jin.</i>

135
00:10:50.320 --> 00:10:52.802
<i>I received your letter.</i>

136
00:10:52.802 --> 00:10:56.831
<i>I hope that you reach your
destination safely.</i>

137
00:10:56.831 --> 00:11:01.121
<i>I hope that I can be of help
to you, if only a little.</i>

138
00:11:05.083 --> 00:11:08.212
<i>"Then, I'll follow you."</i>

139
00:11:09.625 --> 00:11:11.255
"But until then, goodbye."

140
00:11:12.182 --> 00:11:15.575
By "where you are,"
she means Heaven.

141
00:11:15.575 --> 00:11:17.418
And by, "I'll follow you,"
she means...

142
00:11:17.418 --> 00:11:18.635
Does she mean that she'll kill herself?

143
00:11:18.635 --> 00:11:20.841
I thought the same thing, too.

144
00:11:20.841 --> 00:11:23.096
How could a nine year old
think of committing suicide?

145
00:11:24.197 --> 00:11:26.091
While Hye Na was walking
down to the harbor

146
00:11:26.091 --> 00:11:28.451
she kept on looking
at the birds that were flying.

147
00:11:29.081 --> 00:11:33.283
So, on the day she went to the harbor,
she followed Oh Cheol.

148
00:11:33.283 --> 00:11:35.596
I feel like this totally makes sense.

149
00:11:36.634 --> 00:11:39.607
Um, there are other things
that you also need to see.

150
00:11:39.607 --> 00:11:42.756
I found these among the temporary
homeroom teacher's records.

151
00:11:42.756 --> 00:11:46.950
And there's a part where Hye Na clearly
confesses that her mom abused her.

152
00:11:49.001 --> 00:11:52.639
<i>[Consultation Record Card]</i>

153
00:11:59.610 --> 00:12:00.952
Aren't you going to sleep?

154
00:12:01.683 --> 00:12:04.046
I feel like I'll go crazy
if I just sit still.

155
00:12:12.236 --> 00:12:14.860
I shouldn't have given birth to her.

156
00:12:16.220 --> 00:12:18.510
I shouldn't have given birth to her!

157
00:12:19.683 --> 00:12:20.857
But I...

158
00:12:23.173 --> 00:12:25.951
why did I give birth to her?

159
00:12:28.919 --> 00:12:30.113
Honey.

160
00:12:31.817 --> 00:12:33.897
Hold me, please.

161
00:12:59.259 --> 00:13:00.541
Oh yeah.

162
00:13:00.541 --> 00:13:03.485
Don't touch the electric kettle.

163
00:13:03.485 --> 00:13:05.850
And be careful when you use
the hot water at the sink, too.

164
00:13:05.850 --> 00:13:07.970
And be careful when you
jump on the bed.

165
00:13:07.970 --> 00:13:09.519
And don't open the door for anyone.

166
00:13:09.519 --> 00:13:10.558
Okay.

167
00:13:10.558 --> 00:13:12.158
I'll be right back after having dinner.

168
00:13:12.158 --> 00:13:14.248
I won't be back too late,
so don't worry, okay?

169
00:13:14.248 --> 00:13:16.130
All right, I got it.

170
00:13:16.621 --> 00:13:18.312
So hurry up and go.

171
00:13:36.730 --> 00:13:41.591
Location of emergency shelters.

172
00:13:55.273 --> 00:13:56.798
<i>To be honest...</i>

173
00:13:57.721 --> 00:14:01.182
there were many times that I thought
that it'd be nice if she died.

174
00:14:02.609 --> 00:14:04.238
But, Honey...

175
00:14:07.412 --> 00:14:09.471
Why does my heart feel like...

176
00:14:09.961 --> 00:14:11.755
it'll shatter?

177
00:14:15.775 --> 00:14:17.081
It hurts...

178
00:14:18.951 --> 00:14:20.870
so much.

179
00:14:46.595 --> 00:14:48.601
Is that you, Soo Jin?

180
00:14:49.639 --> 00:14:52.270
These are Yi Jin's twins.
Seven years old.

181
00:14:52.270 --> 00:14:54.095
Their names are Tae Hoon and Tae Mi.

182
00:14:54.095 --> 00:14:56.990
- Hello!
- Hello!

183
00:14:58.091 --> 00:14:59.447
Hi there.

184
00:14:59.447 --> 00:15:01.604
Big Sis!

185
00:15:01.604 --> 00:15:05.548
Big Sis! It's been so long!

186
00:15:05.548 --> 00:15:06.952
It's been a while.

187
00:15:06.952 --> 00:15:09.287
Oh, sorry. I ate a little
before you got here.

188
00:15:09.287 --> 00:15:11.426
I left work for a bit
even though we're busy

189
00:15:11.426 --> 00:15:13.278
just so that I could see you.

190
00:15:14.130 --> 00:15:15.330
You're here, Big Sis?

191
00:15:15.330 --> 00:15:17.908
This is about to overflow,
so I can't come out to greet you.

192
00:15:23.267 --> 00:15:25.677
- Wow!
- Wow!

193
00:15:25.677 --> 00:15:28.201
- Wow, I'm so hungry!
- You like crab, right?

194
00:15:28.201 --> 00:15:31.006
I went to Noryangjin this morning
to make you some crab stew.

195
00:15:31.006 --> 00:15:33.616
Wow, this is so good!

196
00:15:33.616 --> 00:15:35.119
But I have to go now.

197
00:15:35.119 --> 00:15:36.544
You should eat more before you go.

198
00:15:36.544 --> 00:15:39.336
I was planning to leave after I just
got a glimpse of Big Sis's face.

199
00:15:40.076 --> 00:15:42.528
It's so nice to see your face, Big Sis!

200
00:15:42.528 --> 00:15:45.254
You'll be in Seoul until
the weekend, right? I'll call you.

201
00:15:45.254 --> 00:15:46.528
Big Sis Yi Jin.

202
00:15:46.528 --> 00:15:48.086
The food was so delicious.

203
00:15:48.086 --> 00:15:50.062
Your kimchi casserole is
truly a work of art.

204
00:15:50.062 --> 00:15:51.476
I'll be going now, Mom!

205
00:15:51.476 --> 00:15:52.707
Your auntie is leaving now, kids!

206
00:15:52.707 --> 00:15:54.749
- See you later!
- See you later!

207
00:15:55.652 --> 00:15:57.836
That's what she's been like lately

208
00:15:57.836 --> 00:16:01.085
since she became a reporter
at a daily newspaper last month.

209
00:16:01.085 --> 00:16:02.231
That's great for her.

210
00:16:02.231 --> 00:16:04.134
And she causes trouble every day.

211
00:16:04.134 --> 00:16:06.359
I'm worried that she'll
get fired one of these days.

212
00:16:06.359 --> 00:16:08.929
Well, she works really hard, though.

213
00:16:11.648 --> 00:16:13.286
This is delicious.

214
00:16:13.286 --> 00:16:14.323
Really.

215
00:16:15.403 --> 00:16:18.448
Mom said that you'd probably
want to eat home-cooked food.

216
00:16:18.448 --> 00:16:20.125
She's right.

217
00:16:20.125 --> 00:16:22.120
I did want to eat something like this.

218
00:16:23.392 --> 00:16:25.663
Did you two greet your
big aunt properly?

219
00:16:25.663 --> 00:16:26.999
- Yes!
- Yes!

220
00:16:26.999 --> 00:16:31.275
I thought she'd be huge
since she's called "Big Aunt"

221
00:16:31.275 --> 00:16:33.428
but she's not even that big!

222
00:16:33.428 --> 00:16:35.452
She's similar to Aunt Hyun Jin.

223
00:16:35.452 --> 00:16:38.178
What are you talking about?
I'm so much bigger.

224
00:16:40.018 --> 00:16:43.102
You didn't know that you had
such a big niece and nephew, right?

225
00:16:43.102 --> 00:16:44.432
Yes.

226
00:16:46.130 --> 00:16:48.347
The kids really take after you.

227
00:16:49.269 --> 00:16:52.528
Tae Hoon looks like his dad
and Tae Mi looks like me.

228
00:16:52.528 --> 00:16:53.673
No.

229
00:16:54.391 --> 00:16:56.861
A part of Tae Hoon looks like you did
when you were young.

230
00:16:56.861 --> 00:16:57.980
Really?

231
00:17:58.055 --> 00:18:00.076
My Tae Hoon hates losing.

232
00:18:00.076 --> 00:18:01.624
He has to be number one at everything.

233
00:18:01.624 --> 00:18:03.384
He's just like his dad.

234
00:18:03.384 --> 00:18:07.778
His dad is number one when it comes to
his studies, his work, and drinking.

235
00:18:07.778 --> 00:18:11.928
And my Tae Mi loves all things beautiful.
She's just like me in that sense.

236
00:18:12.438 --> 00:18:14.346
You hate losing too, though.

237
00:18:14.346 --> 00:18:15.467
Really?

238
00:18:15.467 --> 00:18:20.382
She wants to raise her kids to be clever,
so she takes them everywhere.

239
00:18:21.396 --> 00:18:22.814
What about the piano?

240
00:18:23.992 --> 00:18:25.602
I'm not really passionate
about it anymore.

241
00:18:25.602 --> 00:18:28.093
I haven't been passionate about
anything else since I've had my kids.

242
00:18:28.093 --> 00:18:30.844
There are other people besides me
who are good at playing piano

243
00:18:30.844 --> 00:18:33.259
but my kids need me.

244
00:18:33.259 --> 00:18:36.307
Blood relations are such
a scary thing, in that sense.

245
00:18:36.307 --> 00:18:38.667
I don't know what I would've done
if I didn't have my kids.

246
00:18:49.778 --> 00:18:52.395
"Bus ticket."

247
00:18:53.644 --> 00:18:57.999
"Automatic ticket machine."

248
00:19:05.468 --> 00:19:08.032
"Word game."

249
00:19:12.159 --> 00:19:14.395
"When a balloon gets bigger and bigger."

250
00:19:15.766 --> 00:19:17.941
"The road that leads to the ocean."

251
00:19:20.211 --> 00:19:27.813
<i>"The snip-snip sound
of hair being cut."</i>

252
00:19:34.059 --> 00:19:35.999
<i>"Mom."</i>

253
00:19:35.999 --> 00:19:38.182
<i>"The sound of mom laughing."</i>

254
00:19:44.622 --> 00:19:45.936
13 times 1 is 13.

255
00:19:45.936 --> 00:19:47.952
13 times 2 is 26.

256
